For {= opportunity =}+ public infrastructure procurement opportunities in the United States with a source-visible procurement date or milestone during {= target_period =}, name the public procurer/project, locality, and civil/site-work package, and supply a dedicated official readable source for that opportunity (i.e. {= url =}+ URL per opportunity).

The point is neutral public-source provenance for bid/RFP/RFQ/ITB/quote packages and official public notices, not contact research, lead scoring, proposal strategy, supplier recommendations, rankings, or construction/legal/safety suitability conclusions.

The opportunity ought to be a real public-owner/procurer solicitation or official notice for infrastructure-adjacent civil/site/preconstruction work. The source should be an individual bid page, individual procurement notice, direct project manual/specification/proposal package, or direct PDF whose primary subject is the claimed opportunity/package. Omnibus letting books, multi-contract Notice to Contractors PDFs, broad bid-tab compilations, procurement indexes/search pages, and broad multi-opportunity pages are out of scope unless the cited page itself is dedicated to the exact claimed opportunity. Right-of-way vegetation removal and mowing count when tied to infrastructure clearance or travel-way maintenance; routine facility landscaping, generic groundskeeping, operations-only service contracts, completed-project pages, private project trackers, bid-intelligence aggregators, and proposal-advice pages are out of scope. EPC/prime contractors count only when the page states them; missing EPC/prime information does not make an otherwise valid source fail.

Requirements:
- The page should communicate that it is an official or officially hosted public procurement source dedicated to the claimed opportunity, such as a public owner/procurer/agency/utility/authority bid page, an individual official procurement-portal notice, a direct official project manual/specification/proposal package, or a direct official PDF whose primary subject is the claimed opportunity/package.
- The page must identify the submitted public procurer/project, locality, and scope/package well enough to bind the cited source to the claimed opportunity.
- The page must state a concrete in-scope civil/site/preconstruction scope, such as clearing/grubbing, grading, excavation, drainage/stormwater, infrastructure right-of-way vegetation or mowing, access roads, roadway reconstruction, trenching/duct banks, utility/water/wastewater/power/port/dam/restoration civil work, or comparable site-prep/infrastructure construction.
- The page must show a public procurement milestone or date during {= target_period =}, such as posting/release/advertisement date, bid due/opening date, pre-bid/site-visit date, addendum date tied to the opportunity, or comparable official deadline/milestone.
